                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60 p 31/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-23T10:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1925—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Your telegram number 61, December 18, 9 p.m., Have brought all proper
                    pressure and am hopeful of eventual success. Daily unsuccessful attempts to form
                    [government?] have slowed progress.<note n="22" xml:id="d317fn22">In his
                        despatch No. 3496, Jan. 4, 1926 (not printed), the Minister in Latvia
                        informed the Department that the new Cabinet was accepted by the Saeima on
                        Dec. 22, 1925 (file No. 611.60p31/34).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
